1️⃣ Network Troubleshooting Workflow
User symptom: “I can’t access the internet.”

🧩 Step-by-step workflow
Verify physical/network connection

Check Wi‑Fi/Ethernet status

Confirm airplane mode is off

Check IP configuration

ipconfig /all

Look for missing IP, APIPA (169.x.x.x), or wrong gateway

Test DNS resolution

Resolve-DnsName www.microsoft.com

If fails → DNS issue

Test internet connectivity

Ping 8.8.8.8

Ping www.microsoft.com

Check gateway reachability

Ping default gateway

If unreachable → LAN issue

Check proxy settings

netsh winhttp show proxy

Check firewall/VPN

Disable VPN temporarily

Check firewall rules

🎯 Resolution examples
Restart DNS Client service

Reset network stack (netsh winsock reset)

Fix incorrect static IP

Remove stuck proxy settings
